## Prevention Strategies

### 1. Avoid Redirect Parameters
Design your application to minimize the need for dynamic redirect parameters. Pre-determined flows are always safer.

### 2. Whitelist Allowed Destinations
Maintain a strict list of approved redirect URLs. This is the most effective defense.

**Example implementation (Node.js):**
```javascript
const ALLOWED_REDIRECTS = [
  'https://trusted-partner.com/callback',
  'https://another-trusted.com/return',
  '/dashboard',  // Relative URLs are safer
  '/profile'
];

app.get('/redirect', (req, res) => {
  const targetUrl = req.query.url;
  
  if (ALLOWED_REDIRECTS.includes(targetUrl)) {
    res.redirect(targetUrl);
  } else {
    res.status(400).send('Invalid redirect target');
  }
});
```

### 3. Validate URL Format
Ensure URLs are well-formed and match expected patterns before redirecting.

```javascript
function isValidUrl(url) {
  try {
    const parsedUrl = new URL(url);
    // Check if protocol is http or https only
    return ['http:', 'https:'].includes(parsedUrl.protocol);
  } catch (e) {
    return false;
  }
}
```

### 4. Check Domain
Verify the redirect URL belongs to your domain or a trusted domain list.

```javascript
const TRUSTED_DOMAINS = ['trusted-partner.com', 'ally.example.com'];

function isAllowedDomain(url) {
  try {
    const parsed = new URL(url);
    return parsed.hostname === 'yourdomain.com' || 
           TRUSTED_DOMAINS.includes(parsed.hostname);
  } catch (e) {
    return false;
  }
}
```

### 5. Use Relative URLs
Use relative paths instead of absolute URLs when possible. This prevents redirecting outside your domain entirely.

```javascript
// Bad - can be exploited
res.redirect(req.query.next);  // Could be external URL

// Good - always relative to your domain
if (req.query.next && req.query.next.startsWith('/')) {
  res.redirect(req.query.next);
}
```

### 6. Implement Hash Verification
Use HMAC-based URL verification as described in the Hash-Based Protection section above.

### 7. Add User Confirmation
Display a confirmation page before redirecting to external sites, allowing users to verify the destination.

```html
<div class="redirect-warning">
  <p>You are being redirected to: <strong id="redirectUrl"></strong></p>
  <p>Click the button below to continue, or go back to safety.</p>
  <button onclick="confirmRedirect()">Continue</button>
  <button onclick="goBack()">Go Back</button>
</div>
```

### 8. Security Headers
Use HTTP security headers like CSP (Content Security Policy) to limit redirect capabilities.

```
Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'self'
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
```

