## CVSS Scoring & Risk Assessment

The CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System) score for open redirect varies based on context:

**Typical CVSS Ratings:**
- **CVSS 3.1 (Low-Medium)**: Basic open redirect to external site
  - Base Score: 4.7
  - Vector: Network-Adjacent, Low complexity, No privilege required
  - Impact: Integrity low (users can be misled)

- **CVSS 5.3 (Medium)**: Open redirect in OAuth/SSO flow
  - Higher impact due to authentication bypass potential
  - Can lead to account takeover

- **CVSS 7.1+ (High)**: Open redirect combined with XSS or other vulnerabilities

**Real-World Examples:**

| Company | Impact | Details |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Twitter | Medium | OAuth redirect vulnerability allowed phishing attacks |
| GitHub | Low-Medium | URL redirect parameter vulnerable in specific flows |
| Google | Low | Temporary redirect to potentially untrusted sites |
| Microsoft | Medium | Windows SSO redirect vulnerability |

