## Summary

Open redirect vulnerabilities remain common despite being well-understood. The key defense is **whitelisting** allowed destinations rather than trying to validate or encode URLs. When redirects are necessary, implement **cryptographic hash verification** using HMAC to ensure only pre-authorized URLs can be used. Always validate server-side and never rely on client-side checks alone.
